    },
    {
      "id": "9102b256a59f664e0e82e2d27797cf9a7d865efb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 176,
        "name": "Liang Zhen",
        "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
        "username": "liangzhen",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-08-16 00:56:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(2 inline comments)\n\nanother thing we might want to fix is:\n\nseq_client_alloc_fid()\n......\n\nrc = seq_client_alloc_seq(seq, &seqnr);\n\nif (rc) {\n    CERROR(\"%s: Can't allocate new sequence, \"\n           \"rc %d\\n\", seq->lcs_name, rc);\n\n    cfs_up(&seq->lcs_sem);\n\n    RETURN(rc);\n}\n\nI think the cfs_up() at here will release the mutex we don't even have.\n\nactually, seq_fid_alloc_prep() and seq_fid_alloc_fini() will change state of mutex (lcs_sem) on return, which is really confusing, I would suggest to cleanup this too.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "061a0d64a4017565582fc36060421fdf8f80095d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 101,
        "name": "Lai Siyao",
        "email": "lai.siyao@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "laisiyao"
      },
      "date": "2011-08-16 03:39:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (2 inline comments)\n\nrc = seq_client_alloc_seq(seq, &seqnr);\n\nif (rc) {\n   CERROR(\"%s: Can't allocate new sequence, \"\n          \"rc %d\\n\", seq->lcs_name, rc);\n\n   cfs_up(&seq->lcs_sem);\n\n   RETURN(rc);\n}\n\nI've added seq_fid_alloc_fini() before cfs_up(), so it's safe here.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
